  "text": "The study of a perovskite-type oxide catalyst with oxygen has shown promising results in the conversion of cornstalk lignin to aldehydes. However, long reaction times could lead to further oxidation of the aldehydes to the acid. The catalyst was also recyclable making it very suitable for use in lignin oxidation reactions [CITATION_1] .",
